a representations of ageing play a role in stereotype formation and even reinforce them. Encountering these stereotypes can negatively impact the self-esteem, health status, physical wellbeing and cognitive performance of older people. This international collection examines different dimensions of ageing and ageism in a range of media. Chapters include explorations of the UK media during the COVID-19 pandemic; age, gender and mental health in Ghana; advertising in Brazil; magazines in Canada; Taiwanese newspapers; comics, graphic novels and more. Bringing together leading scholars, this book critically considers differences in media portrayals and how older adults use and interact with the media.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aAgeism. 0aAging in mass media. 0aMass media and older people. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aBoateng, Doris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalasanti, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastro, Gisela G. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCedeira Serantes, Lucia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Chin-Hui, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristensen, Christa Lykke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDalmer, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilleard, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHearn, Jeff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggs, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuang, Yan-Hua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurd, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/